definitions.definition: To collide with (an object), usually with the intention of damaging it or disabling its function.
examples: The man, driving an SUV, then rammed the gate, according to police.

definitions.definition: To strike (something) hard, especially with an implement .
examples: To build a sturdy fence, you have to ram the posts deep into the ground.

definitions.definition: To seat a cartridge , projectile , or propellant charge in the breech of a firearm by pushing or striking .
examples: After placing the cartridge in the musket, ram it down securely with the ramrod.

definitions.definition: To force , cram or thrust (someone or something) into or through something.
To fill or compact by pounding or driving .
examples: They rammed the earth walls to make them more compact

main_definition: ( ambitransitive ) To collide with (an object), usually with the intention of damaging it or disabling its function.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To strike (something) hard, especially with an implement .
( transitive ) To seat a cartridge , projectile , or propellant charge in the breech of a firearm by pushing or striking .
( transitive , also figuratively ) To force , cram or thrust (someone or something) into or through something.
( transitive ) To fill or compact by pounding or driving .
( slang ) To thrust during sexual intercourse .
